com.percussion.utils.security
Interface IPSPrincipalAttribute

All Superinterfaces:
Principal
public interface IPSPrincipalAttribute
extends Principal

Repesents a named attribute of a subject that may be retrieved by a call to Subject.getPrincipals(IPSPrincipalAttribute). Principal.getName() is called to get the name of the attribute, and getValues() is used to get the value. getAttributeType() defines the type of attribute, e.g. what the attribute defines, since the name may be arbitrary.

For example, one cataloger may provide the email address in an attribute named "email", while another may provide it in an attribute name "mailto". Both attributes should return IPSPrincipalAttribute.PrincipalAttributes.EMAIL_ADDRESS from calls to getAttributeType().
